contents:
Pee Curiam,
This case involves the same facts as appear in No. 146, March Term, 1925, the only difference being that here the proceeding was commenced in the orphans’ court and there in the court of common pleas; since we have decided; in the other case, that the latter court, and not the former, had jurisdiction, it follows that
This appeal is dismissed, the costs thereof to be divided between Orie M. Kariher and the G. W. Johnson Limestone Company.
